{
  "texts": [
    "Permanent laser scanning stations allow studying geomorphological changes of, e.g., dunes or glaciers [25] or [26] for a correlation analysis with InSAR (and GBInSAR).",
    "A significant hurdle associated with these Big Data lies in effectively handling multi-temporal point clouds to extract information and identify patterns of change.",
    "The initial step frequently involves the classification of point clouds, a prerequisite for deformation analysis, as explored in [27] for rock slope monitoring.",
    "In [28], three clustering algorithms (k-means clustering, agglomerative clustering, and density-based spatial clustering of applications with noise) were evaluated for identifying regions exhibiting similar evolution patterns.",
    "A time series-based strategy, as described by [29], utilized a Kalman filter approach."
  ]
}